  <div class="one-third">
    <h3>Naming conventions</h3>
    <p>We have used <a href="http://bem.info/method/">BEM</a> as a methodology for naming and classifying CSS selectors, in order to make them more strict, efficient and informative. <a href="http://csswizardry.com/2011/09/writing-efficient-css-selectors/">Over-qualified</a> selectors and excessive wrappers elements should be avoided.</p>
  </div><!-- end .one-third -->

  <div class="one-third">
    <h3>Alphagov</h3>
    <p>The primary SASS file (main.scss) has a dependency on various functions, variables &amp; mixins within the <a href="https://github.com/alphagov/govuk_frontend_toolkit">Alphagov frontend toolkit</a>. This toolkit should never be edited and should be updated with extreme caution. </p>
  </div><!-- end .one-third -->

